title: College roundup: St. Lawrence plays to scoreless tie
text:
A A 
CANTON — Kelsey West made six saves as the St. Lawrence University women’s soccer team finished in a scoreless tie with Middlebury College in a nonconference game Wednesday night. 
The Saints (9-3-2 overall) used North Country Field for the game, which started at 6 p.m., because Sandy MacAllaster Field does not have lights. 
Kate Reinmuth stopped four shots for Middlebury (5-3-5). 
JEFFERSON CC 6, CAYUGA CC 2 
Taylor Andrews notched her first collegiate hat trick as the Cannoneers wrapped up their season with a Regions 3 victory over at the Duffy Fairgrounds. 
Kerstin Phelps, Tess Khalife and Bryanna Gagnon also scored for Jefferson Community College (4-8-1, 2-3-1). 
Michaela Breeze scored both goals for Cayuga Community College (3-11, 1-5). 
The Jefferson CC men’s team lost to Cayuga CC, 3-1, at the Fairgrounds. No other details were reported.
